  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Driver
    The Driver class is responsible for controlling the flow of the entire program as well as executing it.
    FileChooser
    A class to make working with a file chooser easier for students.
    GameTimer
    This class will create a timer that will be used to time the player when they are colouring in the pages Instance Variable
    Highscores
    This class will create the Highscores panel, and adds the printing button, and the back button to the panel Variables
    ImageDisplay
    Class to display an image and the current location with a + sign
    Images
    The images class contains not only the images in the colouring book and their info, but other information shared by all 3 levels in the game.
    Instructions
    The Instructions class is meant for the user to read before playing the game.
    LevelOne
    The LevelOne class is a JPanel which is reposncible for setting up the game aspects which are unique to Level 1 as well as using PictureExplorer to colour the images appropriately.
    LevelSelect
    This class creates the level select screen Variables x stores the x coordinate where the user has clicked
    LevelThree
    The LevelThree class is a JPanel which is reposncible for setting up the game aspects which are unique to Level 3 as well as using PictureExplorer to colour the images appropriately.
    LevelTwo
    The LevelTwo class is a JPanel which is reposncible for setting up the game aspects which are unique to Level 2 as well as using PictureExplorer to colour the images appropriately.
    MainMenu
    The main menu class creates the main menu screen Variables
    Picture
    A class that represents a picture.
    PictureExplorer
    Displays a picture and lets you explore the picture by displaying the row, column, red, green, and blue values of the pixel at the cursor when you click a mouse button or press and hold a mouse button while moving the cursor.
    PictureFrame
    Class that holds a digital picture and displays it using a JFrame
    Pixel
    Class that references a pixel in a picture.
    Score
    The Score class scores a new score after the user completes a level.
    SimplePicture
    A class that represents a simple picture.
    SplashScreen
    This class creates the starting splashscreen for the game Variables
